  <!-- Main content -->
  <article style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px; background-color: #ffffff;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">

      <!-- Section 1: Routes -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);">
        <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0; line-height: 1.25;">
          Cheshire Train Routes to Manchester: Northern and Avanti Lines
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Two distinct rail corridors connect Cheshire to Manchester. The primary corridor runs from Wilmslow (SK9) and Alderley Edge (SK9 7) via Northern Rail stopping services through Handforth, Heald Green, and Cheadle Hulme to Manchester Piccadilly. Avanti West Coast also serves this corridor with faster non-stop and limited-stop services, giving Wilmslow commuters access to both express and frequent stopping options from the same platforms.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Macclesfield (SK10) sits on a separate route via Stockport, served by both Northern Rail and Avanti West Coast. The Avanti express stop at Macclesfield compresses journey times to 18-22 minutes - faster than Wilmslow on express services despite Macclesfield sitting further from Manchester by road distance.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          The Mid-Cheshire Line is a third, slower corridor serving Knutsford (WA16) and Northwich, running to Manchester Oxford Road rather than Piccadilly. Chester connects via the Cheshire Lines route through Runcorn, terminating at Manchester Piccadilly after a journey of 55-62 minutes.
        </p>
        <div style="background-color: #F5F0E8; border-left: 3px solid #C4933F; padding: 18px 22px; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; margin: 24px 0;">
          <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #3D3020; margin: 0;">
            <strong>What this means for buyers:</strong> buyers in SK9 and SK10 postcodes gain access to express rail services that buyers in WA16 (Knutsford) do not. This is a meaningful quality-of-commute difference that rarely surfaces in Knutsford versus Wilmslow comparisons on property portals. Knutsford's Mid-Cheshire Line operates at half the frequency of Wilmslow, serves a different central Manchester terminus, and posts journey times that are 30 minutes longer. These are structural differences, not timetable quirks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2: Train Times Table -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);">
        <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0; line-height: 1.25;">
          Train Times from Cheshire to Manchester Piccadilly
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
          Journey times and season ticket costs by Cheshire town. Fastest times reflect the quickest scheduled departure on each route. Typical peak times reflect average journey times during the 07:00-09:00 morning peak window.
        </p>

        <!-- Table wrapper for horizontal scroll on mobile -->
        <div style="overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; margin-bottom: 12px;">
          <table style="width: 100%; min-width: 580px; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">
            <thead>
              <tr style="background-color: #F5F0E8;">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8; white-space: nowrap;">From</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8; white-space: nowrap;">To</th>
                <th style="text-align: center; padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8; white-space: nowrap;">Fastest</th>
                <th style="text-align: center; padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8; white-space: nowrap;">Typical peak</th>
                <th style="text-align: center; padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8; white-space: nowrap;">Frequency (peak)</th>
                <th style="text-align: right; padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8; white-space: nowrap;">Annual season</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 500;">Wilmslow</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #444444;">Manchester Piccadilly</td>
