                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">4/hr</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: right; color: #444444;">~£3,800</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; background-color: #FDFCFA;">
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 500;">Alderley Edge</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #444444;">Manchester Piccadilly</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #3D5A3E; font-weight: 600;">29 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">33 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">2-3/hr</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: right; color: #444444;">~£4,100</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 500;">Knutsford</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #444444;">Manchester Oxford Road</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #3D5A3E; font-weight: 600;">52 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">58 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">2/hr</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: right; color: #444444;">~£2,900</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; background-color: #FDFCFA;">
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 500;">Macclesfield</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #444444;">Manchester Piccadilly</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #3D5A3E; font-weight: 600;">18 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">22 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">4/hr (incl Avanti)</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: right; color: #444444;">~£3,600</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 500;">Poynton</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #444444;">Manchester Piccadilly</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #3D5A3E; font-weight: 600;">28 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">32 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">2/hr</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: right; color: #444444;">~£3,500</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; background-color: #FDFCFA;">
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #1C1C1E; font-weight: 500;">Chester</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; color: #444444;">Manchester Piccadilly</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #3D5A3E; font-weight: 600;">55 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">62 min</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: center; color: #444444;">2/hr</td>
                <td style="padding: 12px 14px; text-align: right; color: #444444;">~£5,200</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #888888; margin: 0 0 24px 0; line-height: 1.6;">
          Season ticket prices are approximate, based on National Rail 2025-26 fares. Verify current prices at <a href="https://www.nationalrail.co.uk" style="color: #3D5A3E;" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">nationalrail.co.uk</a> before purchase.
        </p>

        <div style="background-color: #F5F0E8; border-left: 3px solid #C4933F; padding: 18px 22px; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; margin: 8px 0 0 0;">
          <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #3D3020; margin: 0;">
            <strong>Macclesfield vs Wilmslow on commute time:</strong> Macclesfield (SK10) posts the fastest journey time in the table despite sitting 17 miles from Manchester. Avanti West Coast express stops compress the journey to 18 minutes - below Wilmslow's 21-minute best. Buyers comparing SK9 and SK10 on commute alone will find Macclesfield competitive on journey time, with a lower annual season ticket cost. The trade-off is property price: average Macclesfield prices run 25-30% below Wilmslow (Rightmove Q4 2025). For buyers prepared to accept a different town character, the commute numbers alone do not favour Wilmslow over Macclesfield.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3: Wilmslow Station -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);">
        <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0; line-height: 1.25;">
          Wilmslow Station: The Express Commuter Base in SK9
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Wilmslow station is the most service-rich commuter station in Cheshire. With 4 trains per hour during the morning peak and platforms shared by both Northern Rail stopping services and Avanti West Coast express services, it offers a flexibility that no other Cheshire station matches. Commuters can choose between a 21-minute express or a 28-minute stopping service depending on the morning's timing.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Cycle storage bays at the station are used by a significant portion of regular commuters. Many established Wilmslow commuters walk from nearby residential streets rather than drive, particularly those within a 10-minute radius of the station.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Handforth station (SK9 3) provides an alternative for buyers in northern Wilmslow. It sits on the same Northern Rail line, operates with fewer passengers at peak times, and adds approximately 3 minutes to the typical journey. For buyers in streets closer to Handforth than to Wilmslow, it is a practical option that avoids the main station's morning congestion.
        </p>
        <div style="background-color: #F5F0E8; border-left: 3px solid #C4933F; padding: 18px 22px; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; margin: 24px 0;">
          <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #3D3020; margin: 0;">
            <strong>The car park problem estate agents rarely mention:</strong> Wilmslow station's free car park fills before 07:30 on weekdays. Buyers who plan to drive to the station should factor a 10-15 minute walk from surrounding residential streets or budget for a season parking permit. This is a material consideration for buyers purchasing specifically for the commute - the station's train service is excellent, but arrival by car is not as straightforward as online listings suggest.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 4: Knutsford -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);">
        <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0; line-height: 1.25;">
          Knutsford to Manchester: Mid-Cheshire Line Realities
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Knutsford station sits on the Mid-Cheshire Line, a stopping service that terminates at Manchester Oxford Road rather than Piccadilly. Oxford Road is approximately 800 metres from Piccadilly on foot - a 10-minute walk that adds meaningfully to journeys whose final destination is the Piccadilly area, Northern Quarter, or Ancoats. For commuters whose offices sit near Oxford Road, the University campus, or the Deansgate corridor, the difference is negligible.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          The line operates 2 trains per hour at peak times - half the frequency of Wilmslow. Fastest journey time from Knutsford to Oxford Road is 52 minutes, with typical peak journeys running to 58 minutes. Compared to Wilmslow, a typical peak journey from Knutsford takes 30 minutes longer each way.
        </p>
        <div style="background-color: #F5F0E8; border-left: 3px solid #C4933F; padding: 18px 22px; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; margin: 24px 0;">
          <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #3D3020; margin: 0;">
            <strong>The cumulative time cost:</strong> over a 220-day working year, the extra 30 minutes each way from Knutsford versus Wilmslow compounds to approximately 220 additional commute hours - roughly 9 full working days per year spent on trains relative to a Wilmslow commuter. For full-time office workers, this is a real and permanent cost of choosing WA16 over SK9. The calculation changes significantly for hybrid workers: at 2-3 office days per week, the same 30-minute gap adds only 60-90 hours annually, a figure that Knutsford's town character, lower season ticket cost, and in some price brackets lower property prices may absorb comfortably.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 5: Season Ticket Costs -->
      <section style="margin-bottom: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);">
        <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 16px 0; line-height: 1.25;">
          Season Ticket Costs from Cheshire: Annual Outlay by Town
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Annual season tickets represent the most cost-effective format for commuters travelling 5 days per week. The break-even point versus buying daily return tickets sits at approximately 3.5 days per week - below which daily or weekly tickets become cheaper. Monthly season tickets are calculated at 8.7% of the annual price under the standard National Rail formula, giving a proportional monthly cost for those who prefer not to pay upfront annually.
        </p>

        <div style="display: grid; gap: 12px; margin: 24px 0;">
