          Hybrid Working and the Cheshire Commute: 2-3 Days Per Week
        </h2>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          At 2 days per week in the office, daily return tickets are typically cheaper than an annual or monthly season ticket. The break-even against an annual season sits at approximately 3.5 office days per week. Hybrid workers commuting twice weekly should calculate the cost of daily returns - or a weekly season ticket on active weeks - against the annual season price before committing to an upfront purchase.
        </p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">
          Northern Rail and Avanti West Coast both accept contactless payment on many Cheshire routes, removing the need to queue at a ticket machine on variable-frequency days. This flexibility suits hybrid workers whose office days shift week to week.
        </p>
