            <strong>How hybrid working changes the Knutsford calculation:</strong> before 2020, a 5-day commuter comparing Knutsford to Wilmslow was weighing 30 extra minutes each way against lower property prices. At 5 days per week, Wilmslow's time advantage was concrete and annual. At 2-3 days per week, those 30 minutes translate to 120-180 extra minutes per week rather than 300 - a shift that meaningfully closes the practical gap. Knutsford's historic commuter reputation was built in a pre-hybrid world. For buyers whose office commitment is 2-3 days, Knutsford's town, market, and character may now justify closer comparison with Wilmslow than the raw journey time difference suggests.
          </p>
